<p class="courseblockdesc">
Theoretical and practical issues concerning the etiology of reading problems and clinical diagnostic techniques. Children with reading problems are diagnosed and taught in the practicum component. Course Information: Prerequisite(s): <a href="/search/?P=CI%20450" title="CI&#160;450" class="bubblelink code" onclick="return showCourse(this, 'CI 450');">CI&#160;450</a>; and <a href="/search/?P=CI%20503" title="CI&#160;503" class="bubblelink code" onclick="return showCourse(this, 'CI 503');">CI&#160;503</a> or <a href="/search/?P=CI%20504" title="CI&#160;504" class="bubblelink code" onclick="return showCourse(this, 'CI 504');">CI&#160;504</a>; and consent of the instructor. Class Schedule Information:  To be properly registered, students must enroll in one Lecture-Discussion and one Practice.<br />
</p>
